entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An open-source operating system focused on AI decentralization and agent-based development. It aims to foster competition and widely distribute value through its open nature.

entities.name: Eliza v2
entities.description: The second version of the ElizaOS operating system, released in stealth mode with ongoing QA and tune-ups before a public announcement. It represents an advancement in the ElizaOS platform.

entities.name: The Org
entities.description: An upcoming feature or release for ElizaOS that will launch after v2, focusing on pre-configured intelligent agents with specific roles. It is intended to make ElizaOS more accessible to non-technical users.

entities.name: Eli5
entities.description: An agent designed to function as a community manager within 'The Org', a future ElizaOS feature. It is also involved in discussions around token staking.

entities.name: Eddy
entities.description: An agent designed to function as a developer relations representative within 'The Org', a future ElizaOS feature. It is also involved in discussions around token staking.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform that provides version control using Git, enabling collaborative software development through features like repositories, pull requests, and issue tracking. It is a central hub for open-source development.

entities.name: Clement Delangue
entities.description: An individual who advocates for open-source AI development, emphasizing its role in fostering competition and decentralizing value, contrasting it with closed-source AI which he believes will destroy jobs.

entities.name: Dankvr
entities.description: An individual developing tools for community governance that consolidate data from platforms like GitHub, Discord, and Twitter to create interactive content and reduce participation barriers.

entities.name: Shaw
entities.description: An individual who made a prediction about rapid advancements in AI development frameworks, specifically suggesting that self-optimizing PyTorch is imminent.

entities.name: PyTorch
entities.description: An open-source machine learning framework developed by Meta AI. It is known for its flexibility and use in research and production for AI and deep learning applications.

entities.name: Jin
entities.description: A community member involved in developing a survey bot that generates AI questions and answers from trending data and who agreed on the benefit of UI theme customization for ElizaOS.

entities.name: Kenk
entities.description: A community member responsible for managing channel permissions and member access within the ElizaOS ecosystem.

entities.name: Amiko
entities.description: A hardware device scheduled for release in July that will offer support for the ElizaWakesUp team's application, potentially expanding ElizaOS's reach to consumer hardware users.

entities.name: ElizaWakesUp
entities.description: A team that has an app currently on TestFlight which will be supported by the upcoming Amiko hardware device.

entities.name: auto.fun
entities.description: A platform or protocol that allows for staking of established tokens, with discussions around its implementation for tokens like Eli5 and Eddy within the ElizaOS ecosystem.

entities.name: The AI Council
entities.description: A group or organization whose discussions generate trending data used for creating AI-generated questions and answers via a survey bot.

entities.name: Windows
entities.description: A widely used graphical operating system developed by Microsoft, noted for its desktop environment and software compatibility. It is a target platform for ElizaOS agent development.

entities.name: WSL
entities.description: Windows Subsystem for Linux, a compatibility layer that allows running Linux binary executables natively on Windows. It is used as a solution for troubleshooting path-related issues with ElizaOS agents on Windows.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A voice over IP (VoIP) and instant messaging social platform designed for communities to communicate through text, image, video, and audio in private group chats or public channels. It's a key platform for ElizaOS community interaction.

entities.name: Twitter
entities.description: A social media platform where users can post and interact with messages known as 'tweets'. It is a significant channel for communication, news dissemination, and is a target for agent development within ElizaOS.

entities.name: TestFlight
entities.description: A service provided by Apple that allows developers to distribute pre-release versions of their iOS, iPadOS, macOS, watchOS, and tvOS apps to external testers. The ElizaWakesUp team's app is currently available on TestFlight.

entities.name: Base
entities.description: An Ethereum L2 blockchain designed for consumer applications, built in partnership with Coinbase. It is known for its developer-friendly environment and low transaction fees.

entities.name: Armaniferrante
entities.description: An individual who shared a tweet emphasizing the importance of source code transparency for decentralization and that private source code carries the same risks as a centralized operator.

entities.name: Brave
entities.description: A free and open-source web browser focused on privacy and security, which actively blocks ads and trackers. It is presented as an alternative to Chrome, especially concerning ad-blocking capabilities.

entities.name: Chrome
entities.description: A widely used freeware, cross-platform, proprietary web browser developed by Google. It is noted for its speed, simplicity, and extensibility, but also for recent changes affecting ad-blocker support.

entities.name: Meta AI
entities.description: The artificial intelligence research division of Meta Platforms, responsible for developing advanced AI technologies and products, including the PyTorch machine learning framework.

entities.name: Apple
entities.description: A multinational technology company that designs, develops, and sells consumer electronics, computer software, and online services. They provide services like TestFlight for app distribution.

entities.name: Microsoft
entities.description: A multinational technology corporation that develops, manufactures, licenses, supports, and sells computer software, consumer electronics, personal computers, and related services and solutions. They are the developers of the Windows operating system and WSL.

entities.name: Coinbase
entities.description: A publicly traded company that operates a cryptocurrency exchange platform. They are partners in the development of the Base L2 blockchain.
